 The most coveted prize in British and Irish music, the “Mercury Prize” was awarded to 21-year-old British-Nigerian artist, Dave in a ceremony held at the Eventim Apollo in Hammersmith, London few days ago. Dave whose full name is David Orobosa Omoregie collected the winner’s trophy and cheque for £25,000, and then performed “Psycho” from his winning album. Dave in his acceptance speech said; I want to firstly thank God. I want to invite my mum up onto stage. I want to thank everyone that made this happen, I want to thank all of the exceptional musicians who performed tonight…I respect you all so highly. I thank my mum, my family, my friends.   This moment right here ❤❤ David Orobosa Omoregie, popularly known as Dave, calls up his mum on stage after winning the 2019 Mercury Prize for his album "Psychodrama" . Video: @bbcradio1 #BellaNaija bellanaija.com A post shared by  BellaNaija (@bellanaijaonline) on Sep 22, 2019 at 2:11am PDT //www.instagram.com/embed.js The post Watch the Beautiful Moment British-Nigerian Singer Dave Called his Mom on Stage after Winning the 2019 Mercury Prize appeared first on BellaNaija – Showcasing Africa to the world. Read today!. Source: Bella Naija